What information does the `getlastimportfrom` command return?

The `getlastimportfrom` command returns two objects: "lastimport" and "lastconfirmednotarization". "lastimport" contains information about the last import from the specified system on this chain, and "lastconfirmednotarization" contains information about the last confirmed notarization of the specified system on this chain.

getlastimportfrom "systemname" Returns the last import from a specific originating system. Arguments 1. "systemname"           (string, optional) name or ID of the system to retrieve the last import from Result:  {   "lastimport" :         (object) last import from the indicated system on this chain    {    }   "lastconfirmednotarization" :  (object) last confirmed notarization of the indicated system on this chain    {    }  } Examples: > verus getlastimportfrom "systemname" > curl --user myusername --data-binary '{"jsonrpc": "1.0", "id":"curltest", "method": "getlastimportfrom", "params": ["systemname"] }' -H 'content-type: text/plain;' http://127.0.0.1:27486/
